claim.claim-text:
14. The pipe according according to claim 13, the process further comprising the steps of:
(i) polymerizing, in a first polymerization stage, said low molecular weight ethylene homopolymer component (B-1-1) in the presence of a polymerization catalyst, hydrogen, ethylene and optionally an inert diluent to produce an ethylene homopolymer having a weight average molecular weight of from 5000 g/mol to 70000 g/mol which constitutes from 49 to 59% by weight of the multimodal ethylene copolymer (B-1); and
(ii) polymerizing, in a second polymerization stage, said high molecular weight ethylene copolymer component (B-1-2), which is a copolymer of ethylene and one or more alpha-olefin comonomers having from 4 to 10 carbon atoms, in the presence of a polymerization catalyst, ethylene, at least one alpha-olefin comonomer having from 4 to 10 carbon atoms, and optionally hydrogen and/or an inert diluent to produce a copolymer of ethylene and one or more alpha-olefin comonomers having from 4 to 10 carbon atoms having a weight average molecular weight of from 200000 g/mol to 700000 g/mol,
which high molecular weight ethylene copolymer component (B-1-2) constitutes from 41 to 51% by weight of the multimodal ethylene copolymer (B-1); and
wherein said first and said second polymerization step are performed as successive polymerization steps with the polymer product produced in any previous step being present in the subsequent step(s) and
wherein said first step and said second step can be performed in any order;
(iii) recovering said multimodal ethylene copolymer (B-1);
(iv) obtaining the coating composition (B-2) comprising 80 to 100% by weight, of the multimodal ethylene copolymer (B-1), optional additives and optional other polymers;
(v) applying said coating composition (B-2) onto the pipe to form the coating layer (B).
